  <section id="our-approach" class="paragraph paragraph--text paragraph-container paragraph-158896">
  <div class="article_wrapper">
    
      <center><h3>Our Approach</h3></center>

  </div>
</section>

  


















 



   <section id="our-strategy" class="why_matter content-paragraph paragraph-container">
    <div class="species_image species_image_reverse">
        <picture >
                <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/content_slide_image/public/2023-02/%C2%A9%20Adriano%20Gambarini%20-%20WWF-US.JPG?h=bc816b12&amp;itok=QsfoJVET" width="1000" height="600" alt="An image taken from the ground looking up at a large tree with lots of branches and green leaves. You can see the sky through the gaps in the leaves." class="image-style-content-slide-image" />




        </picture>

                <div class="copyright--image">© Adriano Gambarini / WWF-US</div>
            </div>
    <div class="content content--padded content_reverse">
            <div class="rich-text-wrapper">
          <p>At WWF we’re uniquely well placed to bring our world back to life. We’ve been protecting nature’s wonders for more than 60 years. And now we’re leading the way not just to protect our natural world but to restore it. We’re working globally with communities, governments, companies and others who have the will to act and transform our world.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>We were the first organisation to develop a science-based strategy that focuses on the links between food, climate and biodiversity loss and we remain at the forefront of this approach. We’re tackling these threats in three key ways: averting dangerous climate change, creating a sustainable food system and restoring threatened habitats and species.</p>


      </div>
              

          <div class="btn-wrap">
                          
                   

     <div class="btn-wrap--item">
     <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/2023-06/WWF-UK-strategy-2021-24.pdf"  class="btn anchor_link  btn--white" ga-on="click" ga-event-category="CTAButton" ga-event-action="click - https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/2023-06/WWF-UK-strategy-2021-24.pdf" ga-event-label=" Our strategy  WWF-UK Strategy 2021-24">
         WWF-UK Strategy 2021-24
     </a>
     </div>

     
     
               
                   

     <div class="btn-wrap--item">
     <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/our-reports/wwf-uk-annual-report-and-financial-statements-2021-22"  class="btn anchor_link  btn--white" ga-on="click" ga-event-category="CTAButton" ga-event-action="click - https://www.wwf.org.uk/our-reports/wwf-uk-annual-report-and-financial-statements-2021-22" ga-event-label=" Our strategy  Annual report 2021-22">
         Annual report 2021-22
     </a>
     </div>

     
     
               
                   

     <div class="btn-wrap--item">
     <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/our-reports/bringing-our-world-back-life-wwf-uk-2024-manifesto"  class="btn anchor_link  btn--white" ga-on="click" ga-event-category="CTAButton" ga-event-action="click - https://www.wwf.org.uk/our-reports/bringing-our-world-back-life-wwf-uk-2024-manifesto" ga-event-label=" Our strategy  WWF UK 2024 Manifesto">
         WWF UK 2024 Manifesto
     </a>
     </div>

     
     
      
     </div>
          </div>
</section>


